{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17628126","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17628126"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T16:54:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T16:54:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17188"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17188","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17188"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9878"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69273"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9878","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9878"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17188"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54726"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4945"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23192"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23196"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69273","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/69273"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA laboratory has identified a genetic variant in a patient\u0027s BRCA1 gene. The variant changes the DNA sequence from cytosine (C) to thymine (T) at position 181, causing a premature stop signal in the protein.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the correct format for reporting this genetic variant?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["BRCA1 c.181C\u003ET, p.(Gln61*)","BRCA1 mutation C to T at 181","Q61* mutation in BRCA1","BRCA1 C181T","Cytosine changed to thymine at 181"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct format \u003Cstrong\u003EBRCA1 c.181C\u0026gt;T, p.(Gln61*)\u003C/strong\u003E follows Human Genome Variation Society (HGVS) nomenclature guidelines. This format includes:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGene name (BRCA1)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECoding DNA reference (c.)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPosition and nucleotide change (181C\u0026gt;T)\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPredicted protein change [p.(Gln61*)]\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect formats are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBRCA1 C181T\u003C/strong\u003E - Lacks proper notation for DNA changes and protein impact\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBRCA1 mutation C to T at 181\u003C/strong\u003E - Uses non-standard descriptive language instead of proper notation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECytosine changed to thymine at 181\u003C/strong\u003E - Too descriptive and lacks gene name and standardised notation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EQ61* mutation in BRCA1\u003C/strong\u003E - Only shows protein change and lacks DNA level description\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStandardised nomenclature is essential for clear communication of genetic findings between healthcare providers and laboratories, preventing misinterpretation of results.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Genetic test results should be reported using standardized nomenclature from the Human Genome Variation Society (HGVS).","Pathogenic variants should be described at both DNA and protein levels when communicating genetic results.","Reference sequences must be included when reporting genetic variants to ensure unambiguous interpretation."],"references":["Turnpenny PD, Ellard S. Emery\u0027s Elements of Medical Genetics E-Book: Elsevier Health Sciences; 2011","den Dunnen JT, Dalgleish R, Maglott DR, Hart RK, Greenblatt MS, McGowan-Jordan J. HGVS Recommendations for the Description of Sequence Variants: 2016 Update. Hum Mutat. 2016 Jun;37(6):564-9. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26931183/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54726"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17188"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"54726","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/54726"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-11T15:30:50+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-11T15:32:12+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9878"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"69273"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level II","synonyms":null,"description":"Understand (interpreting and summarizing information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"ty